Perturbed by the wave of road crashes occasioned by flagrant violations of traffic rules, the new traditional ruler of Uban Garin Fika in Yobe State, Alhaji Umar Musa Muhammad has said that he would partner with the World Bank to bring road safety activities for the benefit of the community. According to him “there are so many things that we need to have, other places are getting, we are lacking behind but with my capacity as the Uban Garin Fika and Member Chartered Institute of Transport Administration, am sure there are a lot of things that I will do, more especially in the areas where we can access funding from the World Bank to enhance road safely activities”. The traditional leader expressed appreciation to Fika Emirate Council Potiskum for finding him worthy of being appointed to contribute his quota in providing a safe and healthy society. World Bank IBB Flood Project 90% Completed, Says Emmanuel NG-CARES To Enable States Earn $20m In 2 Years – World Bank He appealed to the people of the area to stay peaceful, be law-abiding and cooperate with the constituted authorities.